title: Biden Brings Traditional Values to Diplomacy
sub_head: America heads back to the future with a Biden-Harris reboot of Obama-Biden international agreements and alliances.
body:
Your editorial “Biden’s Liberal Internationalists” (Nov. 24) points out that Joe Biden’s choices for national security posts and his selection of John Kerry to be a cabinet-level special envoy for climate all signal that the new governing team will work on behalf of U.S. interests through multilateral institutions. President Trump’s go-it-alone approach will be a bad memory, as America heads back to the future with a Biden-Harris reboot of Obama-Biden international agreements and alliances.
